[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Verifying JDK settings**\n\nI’m setting up to figure out if the JDK 25 Java run fails due to the system property \"java.security.manager=allow\". In JDK 18 and later, calling System.setSecurityManager throws an UnsupportedOperationException unless launched with that property. JEP 411 states that in JDK 18+, setting the security manager is allowed only if the property is unset, defaulting to disallow. I wonder if setting it dynamically is okay. I also need to check if the new OGNL version installs a security manager in its static initializer. I'll inspect further by decompiling.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06e45482ad41ffa9016a3f1afdb5e081969aa9992dc61817f7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPxsFbnttdnbTAnKW0HKQ-oVg_J4dleJPY7mPwK_iZjhU2Go62W9BvvNz6w813tqe7C8ACw8pBC4s6OdCkZyyN91yMUy2FPTpdoLa00ZXW5EEoWmsknHkJY-86veYYubS7vWlnU1vmloMWlgjYJWh7Lg9Xdmx6_RYknZBQcb8_B5ebx7LEdTTf3QRHRogFAMrSaAR2xPV7u4mmsdf0VMc-iEBVVI8I6U1XZZQDufS4myAWuBm_Et_JG5kUstW41_s_yF-87AsQBJoaVAGCrlzG2svkfmqYUEHcXdyr_eVV4O9vICjIta9hsg75jMItb8dIdSoJKaVoX13YmrDaZOxbuSko0SmGJuEfWpc47O9zUBs4w0bo47psfZHfDXKs1a3LYQCFh4_eAm8s6vJ_SLfFbdmkpsjkKcomGx-I1KsYVxVD_lzDsSOMBcKnBXT67dlC2Aqe18EuZU6N6qYXEVaVSP-A4Ex4aREih1eSkaRooRWBO1EkBfzwfxs6xFZNQ6LwJ0xJ0fYFxGae_7ffPyyWoG4UoqE7bHaiAEzXxjHF15OdSntfXUbjtaUkTXt_RDYSJT_PheM0DSWIEzEciGokoj-BZ1iTHnZ4AxpktQS8OFbXNvJitlj2xAHufeKO4LN_FY-lKLWAZBCU9AH5JBgAP8OmDNmDWkNermIpzER_j4p4R22BFx-PSkzVUlSaOpw9XvjX9q6zyV6lUhsgyvNjPnvu9BREUrgtBfXCyo7O6LkzZ5xjONbXW7wevVJt_dB7f0rzXLrgjgV8uwi9HcIUoHSpC6GW01GSTndYVmAvzYa88wI9LuMleQAyUoON4ygIiNXUxSHjX9GFJpnvNDhwe8VDgRYlX2p_rqNChacSOlhV7tALNyxwUE02Z84iu-ede4wq2hVPpPD7b1KIQOTdPyEL1YhXMLtb41tLq5qRzMpQ_DhlqkC5ZdCbLhAzHROHJA2rJMevUKVTqII84I3DTnms2tlIBWPF_Ndu14FXJ3FfeUL05TME7UUKBpnYzYeLoYLvtWaip3FV_8jdo0Jrv2YvLPVeP9i-pl3lhyJzB6t_c6OQuZwbn3paaSTjB3R7eFssp-_XcWU0VCRrpgIyQBilj4_tBUy65R1HnZSm7GcNkO7v1UE-lLhY2